			<div id="question">
				<p>There are 2 points placed at random in a rectangle with the sides 24 and 7. What is the maximum limit to the distance that seperates them.</p>
			</div>

			<div id="answer_check_div">
				<input name="input_ans_4" id="input_ans_4" type="text">
				<input type="button" name="check_ans_button" value="Check Answer" onclick="check_ans_4()"/>

				<div id="correct_4"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Correct</p>
				</div>

				<div id="incorrect_4"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Incorrect</p>
				</div>
			</div>


			<div id="display_answer">
				<input type="button" name="answer" value="Answer" onclick="show_ans_4()" />

				<div id="answer_4"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>The furthest apart they could be is infinitesimally close to two opisite corners. The distance between these corners is 25 so the two points cannot be closer.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

