		<div id="question_5">
			<div>
				<h2>Question 5</h2>
			</div>
			<div id="question">
				<p>Two Mathematicians are discussing their children. One says she has three children. The product of their ages equals 36 and the sum of their ages is the same as their house number. The other Mathematician says there isn't enough information to figure out the childrens ages. The first mathematician then says "well my youngest child would like to be an astronaut". How old is the youngest child?</p>
			</div>

			<div id="answer_check_div">
				<input name="input_ans_5" id="input_ans_5" type="text">
				<input type="button" name="check_ans_button" value="Check Answer" onclick="check_ans_5()"/>

				<div id="correct_5"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Correct</p>
				</div>

				<div id="incorrect_5"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>Incorrect</p>
				</div>
			</div>


			<div id="display_answer">
				<input type="button" name="answer" value="Answer" onclick="show_ans_5()" />

				<div id="answer_5"  style="display:none;" class="answer_list" > 
					<p>36 needs 3 factors, there are 2 groups of factors: (3,3,4) and (2,3,6). Since there is a youngest child, the ages of the children are 2,3,6.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

		</div>	
